sub_title: National Public Health Laboratory Data Analyst, AMREF Global Fund Program, Nairobi Kenya
summary: I am a highly motivated and experienced data analytics specialist with a strong background in Biostatistics and Public health data management. With 15 years of experience, I have enhanced data quality in National TB Prevalence Surveys in Kenya, Eswatini, Botswana, and Lesotho. I led data management teams to test a 2-dose heterologous Ebola vaccine regimen in Sierra Leone. In addition, I led the data analytics and data management task force evaluating the mortality and morbidity of tobacco smoking in Kenya. I supported data management, analysis, and reporting in MOH, KEMRI, and donor offices, namely the Global Fund (GF), CDC, and LSHTM. I am passionate about data analytics; I have built the capacity for MPH students at Jaramogi Oginga Odinga University of Science and Technology (JOOUST) and Maseno University on Biostatistics, Epidemiological methods, and data analytic skills. He recently worked on enhancing Data Quality Review (DQR) in Rwanda.
